news.title: UP-RERA sends 250 possession related cases to courts of adjudicating officers
news.para: Sanjay Bhoosreddy, chairman, UP-RERA reviewed the status of compliance of the orders passed on the complaints of the allottees and realized that the promoters were trying to linger the delivery of possession to the allottees besides the orders for delivery of possession within a specified period of time.

news.title: Railways incurred Rs 835 crore loss due to ‘improper’ decision of land deal: CAG
news.para: CAG’s compliance audit report mentioned that the railway ministry in March 2018 gave “in principle” for an MoU between RLDA and IRCON and get lease premium upfront by transferring the development of land lease rights to the PSUs for generation of no-fare revenue for 2017-18.

news.title: Aadhar Housing Finance net profit jumps 37% to Rs Rs 200 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: The total assets under management for the housing finance company stood at Rs. 21,726 crore, a 21% growth on year, from Rs. 17,947 crore

news.title: Piramal Capital gets creditor status in Radius Project's 5.4-acre Mumbai project
news.para: The National Company Law Tribunal ruled in favor of Piramal Capital & Housing Finance in a dispute over a 5.4-acre land parcel in Mumbai. The tribunal validated the financial claims by Piramal, resolving a legal battle involving J.C. Flowers Asset Reconstruction and confirming the legality of subsequent mortgages on the Avenue 54 project.

news.title: Blackstone to sell 33 crore units in Nexus Select Trust for nearly Rs 4,500 crore
news.para: According to sources, Blackstone plans to sell 33 crore units in Nexus Select Trust at a floor price of Rs 135 apiece. Block deal is likely to happen on Friday. Blackstone intends to monetise its investment through this block deal.

news.title: Birla Corporation's profit falls 45.4% to Rs 32.6 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Birla Corporation's revenue from operations was down 9 per cent to Rs 2,190.37 crore during the quarter under review. It was at Rs 2,407 crore in the corresponding period a year ago.

news.title: ED attaches Rs 113-crore worth assets of Krrish Realtech and Brahma City
news.para: A provisional order was issued under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) on August 6 to attach the properties worth Rs 113.03 crore in the case of Amit Katyal, Krrish Realtech Pvt. Ltd. and Brahma City Pvt. Ltd., the Enforcement Directorate said in a statement.

news.title: Sobha's net profit falls 50% to Rs 6 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Sobha's otal income also declined to Rs 669.85 crore during the April-June period of this fiscal year from Rs 939.24 crore a year ago, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Godrej properties, Sobha among top bidders for Greater Noida land
news.para: The Greater Noida authority had come up with auction of five land parcels for Rs 738 crore and managed to sell it for Rs 1,500 crore.

news.title: Hong Kong court adjourns Shimao Group's liquidation petition
news.para: Since the Chinese property sector plunged into a debt crisis in 2021, numerous developers, including major players like China Evergrande Group, have been hit with liquidation lawsuits from creditors, with some firms already ordered to dissolve.

news.title: Ajmera Realty & Infra's profit up 49% to Rs 31.43 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 196.15 crore in the April-June period of this fiscal from Rs 117.57 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Unitech reports net loss of Rs 1,206 crore in Q1FY25
news.para: Total income declined to Rs 84.04 crore in the April-June quarter of this fiscal from Rs 91.09 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.Unitech reports net loss of  Rs 1,206 crore in Q1FY25

news.title: Incuspaze leases four lakh sq ft office space in Noida from Bhutani Infra
news.para: Sanjay Chatrath, Managing Partner, Incuspaze, said, "Our recent expansions, including significant leases in Gurgaon, Bangalore, Mumbai, Pune, Jaipur and Lucknow, highlight our dedication to meeting the rising demand for flexible workspaces across the nation."

news.title: Rainwater harvesting made mandatory for all new buildings in Rajasthan
news.para: As per govt notification, which comes into effect immediately, the PHED will not sanction drinking water connections to those who do not comply with the order.

news.title: Grihum Housing Finance's net profit up 77% to Rs 46 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: “Our organisation now serves more than 80,000 customers. The Company is proactively aligned with regulators and financial institutions, and we have registered stable growth”, said Manish Jaiswal, Managing Director and Chief Executive Officer of Grihum Housing Finance Limited.

news.title: Ireland: IRES to pursure growth, sell less efficient units
news.para: Ireland's largest private residential landlord announced the review in January and said it would consider a potential sale or merger, asset disposals and new strategic initiatives, along with a review of its status as a listed REIT.

news.title: RBI keeps repo rate unchanged at 6.5%
news.para: Four out of the six members of MPC voted in favour of the rate decision. The panel, whose four-year term ends in October, also decided to retain a policy stance at "withdrawal of accommodation" to aid MPC's focus on bringing inflation towards its 4 per cent target.

news.title: South Korea to boost supply in the real estate market in bid to curb price rises
news.para: The real estate market snapped a six-month run of declines in June, as prices in the capital Seoul jumped by the most in 2-1/2 years, raising concerns among policymakers of a spike in household debt in what is already one of the world's most-indebted countries.

news.title: Tender released for TIDEL park construction in Madurai
news.para: According to the tender, the project will include a ground floor, 12 additional floors and a terrace, along with civil construction, interior finishing work, and other allied development tasks.

news.title: Mhada lottery for 2,030 flats in Goregaon, Powai, Malad on September 13
news.para: The draw will feature 359 flats for the economically weaker section (EWS), 627 flats for the lower income group (LIG), 768 flats for the middle-income group (MIG) and 276 flats for the higher income group (HIG).
